# .trivyignore

# CVE-2026-8376: Perl heap buffer overflow when compiling regex with a
# repeated fixed string -- only affects 32-bit Perl builds. Our base image
# (python:3.12-slim-bookworm) is amd64/64-bit; the overflow condition cannot
# trigger on a 64-bit build. Architecture-inapplicable.
CVE-2026-8376

# CVE-2026-42496: Archive::Tar (perl-archive-tar) path traversal via crafted
# symlinks during extraction (_make_special_file does not validate symlink
# targets). App contains no Perl invocation and no archive/tar extraction
# of any kind -- inherited from base image only, code path unreachable.
CVE-2026-42496

# CVE-2026-9538: perl-Archive-Tar denial of service via a crafted tar header
# with an oversized entry size field. Same package and same reasoning as
# CVE-2026-42496 above -- no Perl invocation, no archive/tar extraction
# anywhere in this app, inherited from base image only.
CVE-2026-9538

# CVE-2026-42497: perl-Archive-Tar arbitrary file modification via crafted
# hardlinks during archive extraction. Same package and same reasoning as
# CVE-2026-42496 above -- code path unreachable, no extraction logic exists
# in this app.
CVE-2026-42497

# CVE-2026-54369: libacl symlink traversal privilege escalation via ACL
# functions (getfacl/setfacl and related library calls). App does no ACL
# manipulation of any kind -- Dockerfile uses a plain `chown` at build time
# only, and the running app (FastAPI/uvicorn) never touches POSIX ACLs at
# runtime. Inherited from base image only, code path unreachable.
CVE-2026-54369

# CVE-2026-41992: GNU gzip global buffer overflow in the LZH decompression
# path (SCO compress compatibility mode). App never invokes gzip/gunzip and
# has no decompression logic of any kind -- the gzip binary is present only
# as a base Debian package, never called by this app at runtime.
CVE-2026-41992

# CVE-2025-69720: ncurses buffer overflow that may lead to arbitrary code
# execution. ncurses is a terminal/cursor-control library; this app is an
# HTTP service (FastAPI/uvicorn) with no TTY or terminal UI of any kind, and
# nothing in this app links against or invokes ncurses. Inherited from base
# image only, code path unreachable.
CVE-2025-69720

# Base image CVEs pending upstream fix -- tracked in issue #X
CVE-2026-12087
CVE-2026-48959
CVE-2026-48962

# False positive: Debian's zlib1g package does not compile contrib/minizip,
# so the vulnerable zipOpenNewFileInZip4_64 code path doesn't exist in the
# installed binary. Confirmed via Debian security tracker (status: ignored)
# and aquasecurity/trivy#6722.
CVE-2023-45853

# Requires attacker-controlled arbitrary SQL execution (large ORDER BY
# expression list). App (app/main.py) contains no database access, no SQL,
# and no sqlite3 usage of any kind -- three static FastAPI routes only.
# Vulnerable code path is unreachable.
CVE-2025-7458
